function exportSequenceAudioForAnalysis() {
    try {
        var seq = app.project.activeSequence;
        if (!seq) return JSON.stringify({ error: "No active sequence" });

        // Generate temp file path using proper cross-platform path construction
        var tempFolder = Folder.temp;
        var timestamp = new Date().getTime();
        var outputFile = new File(tempFolder.absoluteURI + "/splice_audio_" + timestamp + ".wav");
        var outputPath = outputFile.fsName;

        // Check if we have audio tracks with content
        var hasAudio = false;
        for (var i = 0; i < seq.audioTracks.numTracks; i++) {
            if (seq.audioTracks[i].clips.numItems > 0) {
                hasAudio = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        if (!hasAudio) {
            return JSON.stringify({ error: "Sequence has no audio clips" });
        }

        // Use AME for export if available
        if (app.encoder && app.encoder.encodeSequence) {
            // Find audio-only preset or use default
            var presetPath = null;
            try {
                // Try to find WAV preset in common locations using cross-platform path construction
                var appDataFolder = Folder.appData;
                var appFolder = new Folder(app.path);

                var presetFiles = [
                    new File(appDataFolder.absoluteURI + "/Adobe/Common/AME/15.0/Presets"),
                    new File(appDataFolder.absoluteURI + "/Adobe/Common/AME/14.0/Presets"),
                    new File(appFolder.absoluteURI + "/MediaIO/systempresets/58534430_4d756c74-6962697400000000/WAV 48kHz.epr")
                ];

                for (var i = 0; i < presetFiles.length; i++) {
                    if (presetFiles[i].exists) {
                        presetPath = presetFiles[i].fsName;
                        break;
                    }
                }

                // Fall back to default preset
                if (!presetPath) {
                    presetPath = app.encoder.getDefaultPresetPath();
                }

content.text:
## Bug Summary

I searched the `splice-cep` directory for hardcoded paths that would break on different Mac configurations and found issues in the ExtendScript file.

## Root Cause

**File**: `/Users/imorgado/SPLICE/splice-cep/jsx/hostScript.jsx`

The `exportSequenceAudioForAnalysis()` function was using string concatenation with forward slashes (`/`) to construct file paths. While this works on macOS, it can cause issues on Windows where paths use backslashes (`\`).

## Issues Found and Fixed

### 1. Temp folder path construction (line 1241-1243)

**Before:**
```javascript
var tempFolder = Folder.temp.fsName;
var timestamp = new Date().getTime();
var outputPath = tempFolder + "/splice_audio_" + timestamp + ".wav";
```

**After:**
```javascript
var tempFolder = Folder.temp;
var timestamp = new Date().getTime();
var outputFile = new File(tempFolder.absoluteURI + "/splice_audio_" + timestamp + ".wav");
var outputPath = outputFile.fsName;
```

### 2. Preset folder path construction (lines 1264-1276)

**Before:**
```javascript
var presetFolders = [
    Folder.appData.fsName + "/Adobe/Common/AME/15.0/Presets",
    Folder.appData.fsName + "/Adobe/Common/AME/14.0/Presets",
    app.path + "/MediaIO/systempresets/58534430_4d756c74-6962697400000000/WAV 48kHz.epr"
];

for (var i = 0; i < presetFolders.length; i++) {
    var presetFile = new File(presetFolders[i]);
    // ...
}
```

**After:**
```javascript
var appDataFolder = Folder.appData;
var appFolder = new Folder(app.path);

var presetFiles = [
    new File(appDataFolder.absoluteURI + "/Adobe/Common/AME/15.0/Presets"),
    new File(appDataFolder.absoluteURI + "/Adobe/Common/AME/14.0/Presets"),
    new File(appFolder.absoluteURI + "/MediaIO/systempresets/58534430_4d756c74-6962697400000000/WAV 48kHz.epr")
];

for (var i = 0; i < presetFiles.length; i++) {
    if (presetFiles[i].exists) {
        presetPath = presetFiles[i].fsName;
        // ...
    }
}
```

## What Was NOT an Issue

1. **Documentation files** (`.md` files) - These contained user-specific paths but are not executable code
2. **Test files** - Already using `path.join(__dirname, ...)` correctly
3. **CSInterface.js** - Delegates to Adobe CEP runtime which handles paths correctly
4. **manifest.xml** - Uses relative paths (`./panel/`, `./jsx/`) which is correct
5. **config.js** and other panel JS files - No hardcoded paths found
6. **`.claude/` directory** - Development artifacts, not deployed code

## Why the Fix Works

In ExtendScript (JSX), the `Folder` and `File` objects handle cross-platform path resolution:

- `folder.absoluteURI` returns a URI format that uses forward slashes on all platforms
- `new File(uri)` creates a proper File object from the URI
- `file.fsName` returns the platform-specific file system path (forward slashes on Mac, backslashes on Windows)

This ensures the code works correctly on both macOS and Windows without any hardcoded path separators.
